{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"source": "pdfs/Population-synthesis-using-incomplete-microsample.pdf", "page_numbers": "[3, 4]", "headings": "['3.1. Travel Survey']"}, "page_content": "3.1. Travel Survey\nThe Swedish Institute for Transport and Communications Analysis (SIKA), through the Riks-RVU 2005-2006 national travel behavior survey, provided the data for the study. The survey was conducted from October 2005 to September 2006 and included 41,000 Swedish total population registry stratified samples aged 6-84. Each survey\nrow is a weighted sample post-stratified by year, area, age, and sex. The regional division is county-level, except for Stockholm County, which is municipal. Age groups are 6-14, 15-24, 25-44, 45-64, and 65-84. For more information about the survey, refer to report by Abramowski and Holmstr\u00a8 om (2007).", "type": "Document"}}